## 4. Database Schema (Mongoose)

### Group Model (`backend/src/models/Group.js`)
Represents an Event.
-   `name`: String
-   `code`: String (Unique 6-digit access code)
-   `photographer`: ObjectId (Ref: Photographer)
-   `photos`: [ObjectId] (Ref: Photo)
-   `participants`: [ObjectId] (Ref: User) - Clients who joined.

### Photo Model (`backend/src/models/Photo.js`)
Represents a single uploaded image.
-   `url`: String (Cloudinary URL)
-   `group`: ObjectId (Ref: Group)
-   `uploader`: ObjectId (Ref: Photographer)
-   `embeddings`: [[Number]] (Array of 512-float vectors, one for each face found)

